===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], River Sioux had a population of 42, with 17 households and 7 families.<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A67530&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 2, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref><ref name="Census2020PL">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/pl?get=NAME,P1_001N,P1_003N,P1_004N,P1_005N,P1_006N,P1_007N,P1_008N,P1_009N,P2_001N,P2_002N,H1_001N,H1_002N&for=place%3A67530&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 2, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

All residents lived in rural areas.<ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A67530&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 2, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

The [[population density]] was 110.4 inhabitants per square mile (42.6/km<sup>2</sup>). There were 28 housing units at an average density of 73.6 per square mile (28.4/km<sup>2</sup>). Of the housing units, 39.3% were vacant; the homeowner vacancy rate was 11.8% and the rental vacancy rate was 0.0%.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

Of the 17 households, 17.6% had children under the age of 18 living in them, 35.3% were [[Marriage|married-couple households]], 5.9% were cohabiting-couple households, 41.2% had a female householder with no spouse or partner present, and 17.6% had a male householder with no spouse or partner present. 58.8% of households were non-families, 58.8% were made up of individuals, and 29.4% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

The median age was 48.0 years. 31.0% of residents were under the age of 18, and 28.6% were 65 years of age or older. By broader age group, 33.3% of residents were under the age of 20, 0.0% were from 20 to 24, 9.5% were from 25 to 44, and 28.6% were from 45 to 64. The gender makeup of the community was 64.3% male and 35.7% female. For every 100 females there were 180.0 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over there were 190.0 males age 18 and over.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

